The paper discusses the development of a Brain-Computer Interface (BCI) using non-invasive electroencephalographic (EEG) signals and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for real-time control. This involves the use of machine learning algorithms for classification tasks, which falls under the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
